# Building & Developing

The easiest way to build and develop Speedith is to install either
Eclipse or the NetBeans IDEs:

    http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/

    http://netbeans.org/downloads/

Download one of the following:

    * the Eclipse IDE for Java Developers, or

    * the Java SE version of NetBeans.



# Dependencies

Right now Speedith depends on the following libraries:

    * iCircles (Inductive Circles), found here:

        http://git.gitorious.org/speedith/inductive_circles.git

    * Apache Commons CLI (Jakarta CLI), found here:

        http://commons.apache.org/cli/

    * ANTLRv3, found here:

        http://www.antlr.org/
